						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">The problem with simply messing with the luminance is that the resulting animation is not linear. IMO, and ideal fade-out animation should have each color turn into black over the same period of time, so that they all reach black at the same time. </div>
<br />Well, personally I prefer when dark color becomes black before light colors for some reason. I think it looks better, but you can disagree (that's why I proposed to do it that way as well for fade-in).
<br />
<br />I'll definitely use my technique for my games, and your table method sound like a terrible waste of ROM to me. It could be of some use if there were more brightness levels available, but for only 4 (5 including black) it's really not worth having all those table arround. But if it works that way for you go ahead for it.</div>

					
